This paper proposes a new coded video acquisition framework that employs multiple cameras to capture high frame rate video. The paper focuses on the development of coded video acquisition techniques and the analysis of their performance. Given the emphasis on video processing and signal recovery, the most likely sub-category is computer vision (cs.CV). However, the paper also addresses issues related to memory speed, shutter speed, and illumination strength, which suggests that it could also be classified under multimedia (cs.MM), information theory (cs.IT), networking and internet architecture (cs.NI), or systems and control (cs.SY).
